description: Handle "git push and bump" as full source push plus version bump
alwaysApply: true
---

# Git Push And Bump Command

When the user says `git push and bump`, interpret it as:

1. Bump the app version using the policy in `versioning-policy.mdc`.
2. Update the source-of-truth app version in `Sources/GuardianHQ/AppMetadata.swift`.
3. If release/build metadata files are already being maintained, keep them aligned with the bumped version.
4. Commit the requested source changes (not just the version file) unless the user explicitly scopes otherwise.
5. Push the current branch to the Guardian GitHub repository.

If current version is `x.y.100`, bump to `(x).(y+1).0`; otherwise bump micro by 1.
